ons. Full of learning, lyricism, and humor, Jews and Words offers an extraordinary tour of the words at the heart of Jewish culture and extends a hand to the reader, any reader, to join the conversation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aHebrew literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aJewsxHistory. 0aJewsxIntellectual life. 0aJewsxOrigin. 0aJudaismxHistory. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Jewish.2bisacsh1 aOz-Salzberger, Fania, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030015647840uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030015677540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300156775423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300156775/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY